This directory holds the build-time payload embedded into the CNS
binary. At build, the CNS image Dockerfile payload stage drops
gzipped binaries (azure-vnet, azure-vnet-ipam, azure-vnet-telemetry,
azure-ipam) and a sum.txt with pre-compression sha256 checksums.

_README and sum.txt are placeholders so the directory exists in
source control. //go:embed picks up everything except files whose
basename starts with _ or .

The corresponding cns/embed/payload.go declares:

	//go:embed fs
	var embedfs embed.FS

so at runtime CNS can extract each gzipped binary to /opt/cni/bin
via the cns deploy subcommand or the in-process daemon bootstrap.
